ubpm(1)                          User Manual                            ubpm(1)

NAME
  ubpm -- usb-based password manager

SYNOPSIS
  ubpm [global options] command [command options] [args...]

DESCRIPTION
  ubpm is an offline password manager designed to run directly from a usb
	drive. it uses aes-256-gcm encryption and argon2id key derivation to ensure
	security of data.

	the vault is stored as a json file in the .ubpm directory on the usb.

INSTALLATION
	build from source:
		$ just build && sudo just install
	
COMMANDS
	init <path>
		initialize a new vault at the specified path. if path is ommited, defaults
		to current directory.

AUTHORS
	developed by dura5ka <dura5ka@proton.me>. for more information,
	see <https://github.com/ubpmandstuff/ubpm>.

